JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South African banks are financially sound and well-positioned to withstand the impact of sovereign credit rating downgrades, Standard Bank, the country&#8217;s second largest lender by value, said on Tuesday.Ratings agency S&amp;P cut South Africa&#8217;s credit rating to junk status on Monday, saying the dismissal by President Jacob Zuma of a respected finance minister heralded a damaging policy shift.